    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul Gibson reports that Americans at Marash, Hadjin, Aintab, Orfa
                            apprehend being massacred. A hostile feeling toward missionaries exists
                            at Erzeroum, Van, Bitlis. Have demanded telegraphic orders to all civil
                            and military functionaries to enforce respect for Americans, which I am
                            informed at the Sublime Porte have been sent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
